gomodel:SYNGO_4074  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1A: DCV secretion from cholinergic motoneurons was assayed using a transgenic strain (nuIs183) expressing the proneuropeptide NLP-21 tagged to YFP exclusively in dorsally projecting cholinergic motoneurons. This strain has been successfully used to assay DCV biogenesis and release. At the trans-Golgi, the proneuropeptide NLP-21-YFP fusion is packaged into DCVs, where it is subsequently processed into active neuropeptides and soluble YFP. YFP-labeled DCVs are then transported to axonal release sites. After fusion, the soluble YFP is released into the body cavity. Here, it is constitutively endocytosed by macrophage-like cells, called coelomocytes. The YFP fluorescence in coelomocytes can, therefore, be used as an indirect readout for DCV release.\n\nFigure 3A: Both an early-stop allele, tbc-2 (qx20), and a deletion allele, tbc-2 (tm2241), had reductions in coelomocyte YFP intensities by 71.36 ± 14.10% and 81.01 ± 4.00%, respectively. Neuron-specific expression of tbc-2 in tbc-2 (tm2241) KO restored DCV exocytosis. Catalytically inactive TBC-2 R689A were unable to restore DCV exocytosis.\n\nTBC-2 is known to be a RAB-5-specific GAP (PMID: 20462958) suggesting that TBC-2 might be regulating the function of Rab-5 in DCV exocytosis.\n\n20/01/2021 Dnyanada:\nInformation on the species of the TBC2 cDNA used for generating genetic lines could not be retrieved. Hence, Q23419 was chosen.. Experimental description: Wild-type tbc-2 were cloned into pGADT7 as prey. The tested plasmids with tbc-2 mutations (table S2) were mixed to a final concentration of 100 ng/μL along with pbluescript. These mixtures were microinjected into C. elegans to generate transgenic lines as described previously (PMID: 20364145)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4074" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_6239" .

